title: Bushfires threaten properties on NSW mid coast
text: 'Leave now': Desperate plea from authorities in NSW mid coast as homes come are threatened by 'catastrophic' bushfires Catastrophic fire danger declared for huge area of NSW on Sunday Record temperatures and high winds made conditions 'as bad as it gets' Fire commissioner said affected residents should flee their homes early National parks and forests would be closed and people advised to avoid them Commissioner said conditions were worse than Black Saturday in 2009 More than 70 fires are burning and firefighters are calling it unconventional Published: 04:32 GMT, 12 February 2017 | Updated: 06:04 GMT, 12 February 2017 76 shares
